args:
Siblings Lowen and Louise have come to the
Halidom seeking aid, and they inform the prince
that a dragon is hunting Lowen as a sacrifice.
The party decides to build a wind shrine
augmented with mana in order to drive off the
troublesome dragon.

O wind! Blowing over hill and dale
We ask this wish of you
May you protect the weak and frail
From evils old and new

O wind! Messenger of the promised land
Your breath bring naught but joy
Wherever you blow and however grand
We'll always your breezes enjoy
Just a little further now. We're almost\nat the Wind Cavern that lies within\nthese woods.
Wait. That's...a castle? But what is a castle\ndoing all the way out here?
Gya! The wind's blowing even more now!
We're out of options—we'll have to see\nif we can take shelter at that castle and\nlook for the cavern later.
We're almost there, Lowen.\nNow take my hand and let's go!
Oh, nothing. I just noticed that the wind\nhad picked up suddenly.
Oh yeah, huh? That's kinda weird.
Something might have happened with\nMidgardsormr. I'm going to go check.
Hey, {player_name}?\nLooks like we've got someone at the gates.
They're gonna get blown away at this rate!
This isn't good. Notte and Cleo, I need you\nto get Elisanne and Ranzal right now!
Come with me—we have to help those\npeople before it's too late!
I'm the ruler of this castle, which is where\nyou guys need to be. It's too dangerous\nto be out here right now!
We are in your debt, sir. But if we don't\nhurry, she's going to—
That is one heck of a squall!\nWhat's going on?!
Why is a dragon pursuing you?
There's no time to explain. I'm going to\nfight, but I need you to look after my\nbrother Lowen. Please!
Wait, you're going to fight the DRAGON?
I don't know what this dragon's deal is,\nbut fighting it alone is suicide.
Yeah. This is all my fault. The dragon\nchose me to be a sacrifice, so that's\nwhy Louise has to protect me.
I'll get the details from you AFTER we\nsave your sister.
Cleo, can you tend to this boy's wounds?\nThe rest of you, come with me!
You are wounded, human. If you stay\nyour current course, you will most\ncertainly perish.
I'll never hand over Lowen to you—\neven if it costs me my life!
This is no business of yours, boy!
Stand down, dragon. You do not want\nthis fight.

Listen to the lady, yeah? I know yer tough
and all, but there's a lot of us here, and
we're pretty good with the pointy end
of a sword.
This is not the end. I WILL come for the\nboy—of this, you can be certain.
Looks like we got her to back off.
For now, at least. Thank you very much\nfor all of your help.
But she said she'd be back, yeah?\nMight not be quite so easy next time.
We must think of a way to keep her from\nreturning. ...Er, does anyone have any\nideas, perchance?
We've heard tale of a place called the\nWind Cavern somewhere in these woods.
Ah, yes. I heard about that from\nthe Windwyrm.
The cavern is filled with curious ore\nthat generates wind mana.
That's right. And we were thinking we\ncould use the power of the wind mana\nthere to deter Garuda.
That's actually why we've come to these\nwoods in the first place.
I'm afraid the cavern is in the very far\nreaches of the forest—there's nothing\naround it for miles in any direction.
Shutting yourself up in there indefinitely\nwould be something of a challenge.
Well, shoot. What do we do now?
What if we all camped out in this\nwind-cave dealie?
We'll bring a buttload of food along,\nsing some songs, tell a few tales...\nIt'll be great!
Hey, yeah! Everyone loves a camping trip!
You both need to take this more seriously.
Ha ha! That's classic Elisanne, right there.\nStill, we can't just abandon these people.\nThere has to be something we can do.
Well, if going to the cave won't work,\nmaybe we can bring the cave to the castle!
I literally JUST told you to take\nthis seriously.
No, wait. Ranzal may be onto something—\nas shocking as that is.
Obviously, it's impossible to move the\nentire cavern. However, we COULD go\nthere and collect some ore.

We could then use it to construct a
small wind shrine inside the Halidom,
which should give it the same effect
as the cavern itself.
And as a bonus, we'd also be able to\nreceive the blessings of wind mana.
I can't believe you'd go to such lengths\nfor a pair of complete strangers.
We can't leave you to solve this all by\nyourself. And honestly, this isn't just\nyour problem.
It's the royal family's mission to correct\ndragons when their behavior is wrong.
You're a member of the royal family...?
If my man {player_name} says\nit's go time, then we go.
It's settled, then. We'll head for the Wind\nCavern, then build a wind shrine right\nhere in the castle!
